Applying Hess's Law
$$
\begin{aligned}
\Delta_{\mathrm{f}} \mathrm{H}^{\circ}= & \Delta_{\text {sub }} \mathrm{H}+\frac{1}{2} \Delta_{\text {diss }} \mathrm{H}+\text { I.E. }+\text { E.A }+\Delta_{\text {lattice }} \mathrm{H} \\
& -617=161+520+77+\text { E.A. }+(-1047) \\
& \text { E.A. }=-617+289=-328 \mathrm{~kJ} \mathrm{~mol}^{-1} \\
